FBIS4-28852 "dreas114_d_94022" FBIS-EAS-94-114 Daily Report 14 Jun 1994 South Korea Kim Pyong-il Reportedly Assumes Military Post Kim Pyong-il Reportedly Assumes Military Post SK1406104394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 1025 GMT 14 Jun 94 SK1406104394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Korean BFN [Text] It is reported that Kim Pyong-il, North Korean President Kim Il-song's second son, has recently assumed an important post in military affairs. Western sources in Beijing who are well versed in North Korean affairs have reported: It has been learned that Kim Pyong-il--whose activities inside North Korea have not been known since he returned to Pyongyang last April, one month after he went to Finland as ambassador--has been appointed to an important post in North Korean military affairs.
